<h1>Rails Table Preferences Demo</h1>

<p>
  Start with the editor and table below to verify preference changes, table
  behavior, and persistence. The screen uses in-memory rows for table display
  and the normal <code>table_preferences</code> table for saved preferences.
</p>

<details class="rails-table-preferences-demo-summary rails-table-preferences-demo-details">
  <summary>Preset, scope, and sample-data checks included in this demo</summary>

  <p>
    The generated demo seeds one shared preset named <strong>共有ビュー</strong>.
    Select it to confirm that a normal user can load a shared preset, cannot
    delete it directly, and saves changes back into an owner preset instead of
    overwriting the shared preset.
  </p>

  <p>
    The demo also seeds one role preset named <strong>担当ビュー</strong> for the
    role key <code>operations</code>. If the host app configures
    <code>scope_context_method</code> to return <code>{ roles: ["operations"] }</code>,
    the selector also shows <strong>担当ビュー [role:operations]</strong> and resolves
    it before the shared preset while no owner default exists.
  </p>

  <p>
    The demo also seeds one organization preset named <strong>東京組織ビュー</strong>
    for the organization key <code>tokyo-hq</code>. If the host app returns
    <code>{ organization: "tokyo-hq" }</code>, the selector shows
    <strong>東京組織ビュー [organization:tokyo-hq]</strong>. With no owner default and
    no matching role default, reloading the demo resolves it before the shared preset.
  </p>

  <p>
    Sample rows intentionally mix statuses, delivery dates, repeated customer
    prefixes, long shipping codes, long delivery notes, and memo lengths.
    Search for <strong>東京</strong> or sort by <strong>納品日</strong> /
    <strong>金額</strong> to make the differences easier to spot.
  </p>

  <p>
    Double-click the resize handle on <strong>配送メモ</strong> or <strong>配送コード</strong>
    to confirm auto-fit, then compare <strong>配送メモ</strong> (wrap),
    <strong>配送コード</strong> (nowrap), and <strong>備考</strong> (ellipsis)
    to see the overflow modes side by side.
  </p>

  <p>
    The table below also keeps <strong>受注番号</strong> pinned inside a dedicated
    horizontal scroll wrapper and shows one grouped header row
    (<strong>受注情報</strong> / <strong>得意先情報</strong> / <strong>配送情報</strong>) that follows the
    current saved visible-column order after reload, so fixed-column and column-group
    behavior can be checked without additional host-app markup first.
  </p>
</details>

<style>
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-scroll {
    max-width: 100%;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-table {
    min-width: 1280px;
    border-collapse: separate;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-table th,
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-table td {
    background: white;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-table__group-row th {
    background: #f3f4f6;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-summary {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #d1d5db;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    background: #f9fafb;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-summary dl {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-summary dt {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #374151;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-summary dd {
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-details summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-details p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-hidden-fields-preview {
    max-width: 100%;
    overflow-x: auto;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid #d1d5db;
    background: white;
    white-space: pre-wrap;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-owner-note,
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-scope-note {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-owner-switches,
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-scope-switches {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-owner-switches li,
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-scope-switches li {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-owner-switch,
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-scope-switch,
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-reset-trigger,
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-failure-trigger {
    display: inline-flex;
    width: fit-content;
    padding: 0.45rem 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid #9ca3af;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: white;
    color: #111827;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-reset-trigger:disabled {
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-owner-switch--active,
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-scope-switch--active {
    border-color: #1d4ed8;
    background: #dbeafe;
    color: #1e3a8a;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-reset-status,
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-failure-status {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>

<%= table_preferences_editor(
  table_key: :rails_table_preferences_demo_orders,
  settings: @table_preference_settings,
  columns: @table_columns,
  title: "デモ受注一覧の表示設定"
) %>

<% demo_hidden_fields_html = table_preferences_hidden_fields(
  settings: @table_preference_settings,
  columns: @table_columns
) %>

<%= form_with url: request.path, method: :get do %>
  <%= text_field_tag :search_word, params[:search_word], placeholder: "得意先名" %>

  <%= demo_hidden_fields_html %>

  <%= submit_tag "検索" %>
<% end %>

<section class="rails-table-preferences-demo-summary">
  <h2>Search form hidden fields preview</h2>

  <p>
    This preview shows the hidden inputs that the existing search form above
    submits from the current saved filter and sort state. It is separate from
    the export payload preview below.
  </p>

  <pre class="rails-table-preferences-demo-hidden-fields-preview"><code><%= h(demo_hidden_fields_html.presence || "No saved filter or sort hidden fields are currently generated.") %></code></pre>

  <p>
    Save a filter or sort, reload, and compare this markup with the search
    results above. Array params keep their <code>[]</code> names, blank values are
    omitted, and saved boolean false values remain visible when they are part of
    the saved preference state.
  </p>
</section>

<div class="rails-table-preferences-demo-scroll">
  <%= table_preferences_table_tag(
    table_key: :rails_table_preferences_demo_orders,
    settings: @table_preference_settings,
    columns: @table_columns,
    class: "table rails-table-preferences-demo-table"
  ) do %>
    <thead>
      <% if @demo_visible_column_groups.any? %>
        <tr class="rails-table-preferences-demo-table__group-row">
          <% @demo_visible_column_groups.each do |group| %>
            <th colspan="<%= group["colspan"] %>"><%= group["label"] %></th>
          <% end %>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
      <tr>
        <% @demo_visible_columns.each do |column| %>
          <th data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="<%= column["key"] %>"><%= column["label"] %></th>
        <% end %>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <% @orders.each do |order| %>
        <tr>
          <% @demo_visible_columns.each do |column| %>
            <% key = column["key"] %>
            <td data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="<%= key %>">
              <% case key %>
              <% when "delivery_date" %>
                <%= l(order[:delivery_date]) %>
              <% when "amount" %>
                <%= number_with_delimiter(order[:amount]) %>
              <% else %>
                <%= order[key.to_sym] %>
              <% end %>
            </td>
          <% end %>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
    </tbody>
  <% end %>
</div>

<section class="rails-table-preferences-demo-summary">
  <h2>Current owner</h2>

  <p>
    Shared presets save back into this owner context when you use
    <strong>Save</strong> or <strong>Save as new</strong>.
  </p>

  <dl>
    <div>
      <dt>Model</dt>
      <dd><%= @demo_owner_summary.fetch("model_name") %></dd>
    </div>

    <div>
      <dt>Display</dt>
      <dd><%= @demo_owner_summary.fetch("display_name") %></dd>
    </div>

    <div>
      <dt>Identifier</dt>
      <dd><%= @demo_owner_summary.fetch("identifier") %></dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

<section class="rails-table-preferences-demo-summary">
  <h2>Owner switch</h2>

  <p>
    Use these demo-only links to switch the active owner and confirm that saved
    presets stay isolated between representative owners.
  </p>

  <% if @demo_owner_switch_ready %>
    <ul class="rails-table-preferences-demo-owner-switches">
      <% @demo_owner_switches.each do |switch| %>
        <li>
          <%= link_to switch.fetch("label"),
                      switch.fetch("path"),
                      class: [
                        "rails-table-preferences-demo-owner-switch",
                        ("rails-table-preferences-demo-owner-switch--active" if switch["active"])
                      ].compact.join(" "),
                      "aria-current": ("page" if switch["active"]) %>
          <span><%= switch.fetch("description") %></span>
        </li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  <% else %>
    <p class="rails-table-preferences-demo-owner-note">
      Keep the host app owner and create at least one more owner record to
      compare save/load isolation here.
    </p>
  <% end %>
</section>

<section class="rails-table-preferences-demo-summary">
  <h2>Current scope context</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>Current context:</strong>
    <% if @demo_scope_context_summary["owner_only"] %>
      owner-only
    <% else %>
      <% summary_parts = [] %>
      <% if @demo_scope_context_summary.fetch("roles", []).any? %>
        <% summary_parts << "roles: [#{@demo_scope_context_summary.fetch("roles").join(", ")}]" %>
      <% end %>
      <% if @demo_scope_context_summary["organization"].present? %>
        <% summary_parts << "organization: #{@demo_scope_context_summary["organization"]}" %>
      <% end %>
      <code><%= summary_parts.join(" / ") %></code>
    <% end %>
  </p>

  <p>
    Use this summary to confirm which scope the preset selector and default
    resolution below should reflect before comparing owner, role, and
    organization behavior.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="rails-table-preferences-demo-summary">
  <h2>Scope switch</h2>

  <p>
    Use these demo-only links to compare owner, role, and organization preset
    resolution without editing controller code between requests.
  </p>

  <% unless @demo_scope_context_toggle_ready %>
    <p class="rails-table-preferences-demo-scope-note">
      Set <code>scope_context_method</code> to <code>table_preference_scope_context</code>
      once to make the owner / role / organization links below drive the demo.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <ul class="rails-table-preferences-demo-scope-switches">
    <% @demo_scope_context_switches.each do |switch| %>
      <li>
        <%= link_to switch.fetch("label"),
                    switch.fetch("path"),
                    class: [
                      "rails-table-preferences-demo-scope-switch",
                      ("rails-table-preferences-demo-scope-switch--active" if switch["active"])
                    ].compact.join(" "),
                    "aria-current": ("page" if switch["active"]) %>
        <span><%= switch.fetch("description") %></span>
      </li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="rails-table-preferences-demo-summary">
  <h2>Export payload preview</h2>

  <p>
    This preview compares the ordered headers and column keys that the current
    saved table settings would pass into the export helper by default and with
    <code>include_hidden: true</code>.
  </p>

  <% export_payload_with_hidden_preview = RailsTablePreferences::ExportPayload.call(
    settings: @table_preference_settings,
    columns: @table_columns,
    include_hidden: true
  ) %>

  <dl>
    <div>
      <dt>Default headers</dt>
      <dd><%= @export_payload_preview.fetch("headers", []).join(" / ") %></dd>
    </div>

    <div>
      <dt>Default column keys</dt>
      <dd><code><%= @export_payload_preview.fetch("column_keys", []).join(", ") %></code></dd>
    </div>

    <div>
      <dt>Include-hidden headers</dt>
      <dd><%= export_payload_with_hidden_preview.fetch("headers", []).join(" / ") %></dd>
    </div>

    <div>
      <dt>Include-hidden column keys</dt>
      <dd><code><%= export_payload_with_hidden_preview.fetch("column_keys", []).join(", ") %></code></dd>
    </div>
  </dl>

  <p>
    Hidden columns stay out of the default payload and appear in the
    include-hidden payload. Change visibility or order in the editor, save once,
    and reload to compare both export-helper results before wiring a host-app
    CSV, Excel, or report export.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="rails-table-preferences-demo-summary" data-rails-table-preferences-demo-reset>
  <h2>Demo state reset</h2>

  <p>
    Use this demo-only button to delete owner-scoped presets for the current
    owner and table, then reload into the seeded shared / role / organization
    baseline without changing code.
  </p>

  <button type="button"
          class="rails-table-preferences-demo-reset-trigger"
          data-rails-table-preferences-demo-reset-trigger>
    Reset demo verification state
  </button>

  <p class="rails-table-preferences-demo-reset-status"
     role="status"
     aria-live="polite"
     data-rails-table-preferences-demo-reset-status></p>
</section>

<section class="rails-table-preferences-demo-summary" data-rails-table-preferences-demo-failure>
  <h2>Async failure check</h2>

  <p>
    Use this demo-only button to make the next preset save, load, or delete
    request fail once. The following retry uses the normal mounted engine API.
  </p>

  <button type="button"
          class="rails-table-preferences-demo-failure-trigger"
          data-rails-table-preferences-demo-failure-trigger>
    Fail next preset request once
  </button>

  <p class="rails-table-preferences-demo-failure-status"
     role="status"
     aria-live="polite"
     data-rails-table-preferences-demo-failure-status></p>
</section>

<script>
  (() => {
    if (!window.__railsTablePreferencesDemoResetInstalled) {
      window.__railsTablePreferencesDemoResetInstalled = true

      const resetStatusElements = () => document.querySelectorAll("[data-rails-table-preferences-demo-reset-status]")
      const setDemoResetStatus = (message) => {
        resetStatusElements().forEach((element) => { element.textContent = message })
      }
      const csrfToken = () => document.querySelector("meta[name='csrf-token']")?.content || ""
      const demoControllerElement = () => document.querySelector("[data-controller~='rails-table-preferences']")
      const collectionUrl = () => demoControllerElement()?.dataset.railsTablePreferencesCollectionUrlValue
      const preferenceUrl = (url, name) => `${url}/${encodeURIComponent(name || "default")}`
      const ownerPreferences = (preferences) => preferences.filter((preference) => (
        preference.editable && (preference.scope_type || "owner") === "owner"
      ))

      document.addEventListener("click", async (event) => {
        const trigger = event.target.closest("[data-rails-table-preferences-demo-reset-trigger]")
        if (!trigger) return

        event.preventDefault()
        if (trigger.disabled) return

        const url = collectionUrl()
        if (!url) {
          setDemoResetStatus("Demo reset is not available until the preset editor is rendered.")
          return
        }

        trigger.disabled = true
        setDemoResetStatus("Resetting owner presets for this demo table...")

        try {
          const response = await fetch(url, { headers: { "Accept": "application/json" } })
          if (!response.ok) throw new Error(`Failed to load table preference presets: ${response.status}`)
          const payload = await response.json()
          const preferences = ownerPreferences(payload.preferences || [])

          await Promise.all(preferences.map((preference) => fetch(preferenceUrl(url, preference.name), {
            method: "DELETE",
            headers: { "Accept": "application/json", "X-CSRF-Token": csrfToken() }
          }).then((deleteResponse) => {
            if (!deleteResponse.ok && deleteResponse.status !== 204) {
              throw new Error(`Failed to delete table preference preset: ${deleteResponse.status}`)
            }
          })))

          setDemoResetStatus("Demo owner presets were reset. Reloading the seeded baseline...")
          window.location.reload()
        } catch (error) {
          trigger.disabled = false
          setDemoResetStatus("Demo reset could not finish. Check the browser console or server log, then retry.")
          console.error(error)
        }
      })
    }

    if (window.__railsTablePreferencesDemoFailureInstalled) return
    window.__railsTablePreferencesDemoFailureInstalled = true

    const nativeFetch = window.fetch.bind(window)
    let failNextPresetRequest = false

    const statusElements = () => document.querySelectorAll("[data-rails-table-preferences-demo-failure-status]")
    const setDemoFailureStatus = (message) => {
      statusElements().forEach((element) => { element.textContent = message })
    }
    const preferenceUrls = () => Array.from(document.querySelectorAll("[data-controller~='rails-table-preferences']")).flatMap((element) => [
      element.dataset.railsTablePreferencesCollectionUrlValue,
      element.dataset.railsTablePreferencesUrlValue
    ].filter(Boolean))
    const requestUrl = (input) => typeof input === "string" ? input : input?.url || ""
    const matchesPreferenceRequest = (input) => {
      const url = requestUrl(input)
      return preferenceUrls().some((preferenceUrl) => (
        url === preferenceUrl ||
        url.startsWith(`${preferenceUrl}/`) ||
        url.startsWith(`${preferenceUrl}?`)
      ))
    }

    document.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
      const trigger = event.target.closest("[data-rails-table-preferences-demo-failure-trigger]")
      if (!trigger) return

      failNextPresetRequest = true
      setDemoFailureStatus("The next preset request will fail once.")
    })

    window.fetch = (...args) => {
      if (failNextPresetRequest && matchesPreferenceRequest(args[0])) {
        failNextPresetRequest = false
        setDemoFailureStatus("One preset request failed as planned. Retry the same action to confirm recovery.")
        return Promise.resolve(new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: "Demo failure" }), {
          status: 503,
          headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" }
        }))
      }

      return nativeFetch(...args)
    }
  })()
</script>